  "texts": [
    "RGB-D technology has advantages such as affordable acquisition, computational cheap 3D reconstruction methods, and low power consumption translated to high autonomy.",
    "However, in many cases, final images may comprise missing values, translated to holes, which must be filled, or depth maps of low resolutions, which must be up-sampled.",
    "Moreover, disadvantages at sensory level are observed.",
    "RGB-D sensors may fail to capture objects and surfaces with reflections, transparencies, absorptive materials, motion blurred, noisy characteristics and errors can be displayed (systematic and random) due to strong light and to their limited scanning speed.",
    "Additionally, low-cost RGB-D sensors cannot provide high quality data."
  ],
